      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can use different "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/caanimation"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " subclasses to animate effects in different ways. For example, a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/cabasicanimation"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " transitions a property from one value to another, and a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/cakeyframeanimation"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " transitions a property through a series of values. You use properties of the animation object to define its timing curve, repeat mode, and other options. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "SceneKit ignores the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/capropertyanimation/1412496-keypath"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of this animation object. Instead, when you attach a property controller to a particle system’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnparticlesystem/1522775-propertycontrollers"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " dictionary, use one of the keys listed in Particle Property Keys to specify which particle property it animates. SceneKit also ignores the animation’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/camediatiming/1427652-duration"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/camediatiming/1427666-repeatcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties. Instead, the controller defines the behavior of the animation’s input value."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
